Hurray!!! we have analysed our data and we are ready to state out the points of our analysis which we inferred out of our data
1. Publish time and trending date have an almost perfect Linear relationship 
2. Youtube places a video in its trending section if it succeeds to get a minimum of 4k views(in a span of 2,3 days which we can infer out of our trending vs publish date graph) and youtube surprisingly trends less than 25% videos with more than 800,000 views
3. Number of Likes is not a factor that is considered for a video to trend on youtube
4. We observe that the majority that is 86% of our videos had less than 2k dislikes and considering minimum views to be 4k and nearly 75% of our views being more than 100k we can infer that 2k is a considerably small number,So it is clear to us that youtube does not encourage videos with a lot of dislikes
5.  Number of Comments also do not play a role in youtube's trending algorithm because there is no minimum number of comments required for our video to trend on youtube
6. The Youtube trending system's algorithm did not change over time but it's certain that the trending system has relaxed its parameters a bit as we can see a change in 15% for dislikes and 22% for views(those are differences in the percentages of the lower end of both dislikes and views), So we can infer that the algorithm has relaxed a bit from 2017 to 2018 when the starting and the ending date of the datasets were compared
